Haniel to Eliminate Third of Jobs at Headquarters, WiWo Reports

-- B y   S h e e n a g h   M a t t h e w s
-- 
2011-10-22T14:11:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-22/haniel-to-eliminate-third-of-jobs-at-headquarters-wiwo-reports.html
Franz Haniel & Cie GmbH, which
controls retail chain  Metro AG (MEO)  and drug wholesaler  Celesio AG (CLS1) ,
will cut almost a third of staff at its headquarters in
Duisburg, Germany,  WirtschaftsWoche reported , citing an
unidentified Haniel spokesman.  About 70 jobs from 250 will be eliminated by the end of
2012, saving the company about 10 million euros ($14 million) a
year, the German magazine said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sheenagh Matthews in Frankfurt at 
 smatthews6@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Benedikt Kammel at 
